# Evaluation and significant experiments

Use this module when variants are compared, model behavior can regress, or quality claims will be shared.

Create one record for a baseline, a decision-relevant variant, a regression check, or a cited final run.
Do not record every trace. Detailed prompts, responses, spans, and metrics may remain in an external system
such as an experiment tracker or observability platform.

Each result should link a stable `run_id` to the relevant decision, code revision, dataset version,
model/configuration, metric definition, API usage, and evidence. Mark invalid and failed runs instead of
silently removing them.

Before publishing a result, verify that the protocol is comparable, the dataset may be referenced, the
metric was defined before interpretation, and limitations are explicit.
